@page "/about"
<PageTitle>About · D365 ERP Command Center</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <div>
        <h1>About this project</h1>
    </div>
</div>

<p class="lead">
    The D365 ERP Command Center is a self-contained Blazor WebAssembly portfolio demo built by
    Keystone Marcy. It models <strong>Alamo Foods Co.</strong>, a fictional San Antonio food
    manufacturer in the middle of a Microsoft Dynamics 365 Finance &amp; Operations roll-out.
    Everything runs entirely client-side in your browser — there is no server or database. The
    sample data is seeded into <code>localStorage</code> on first load, so you can browse,
    edit and explore freely.
</p>

<h2>What this demonstrates</h2>
<div class="persona-grid">
    <FluentCard Class="persona-card">
        <h3>Data Analyst</h3>
        <p>Executive Dashboard and Financial Analytics — KPI scorecards, trial balance, P&amp;L and balance sheet.</p>
    </FluentCard>
    <FluentCard Class="persona-card">
        <h3>D365 ERP Analyst</h3>
        <p>General Ledger, AP, AR and Budget alongside Procurement, Inventory and Sales Orders.</p>
    </FluentCard>
    <FluentCard Class="persona-card">
        <h3>Business Analyst</h3>
        <p>Fit-Gap analysis, the Requirements Traceability Matrix, Test/UAT management and the Process Catalog.</p>
    </FluentCard>
    <FluentCard Class="persona-card">
        <h3>Project Manager</h3>
        <p>Implementation Roadmap, the RAID log and weekly Status Reports.</p>
    </FluentCard>
</div>

<h2>Tech</h2>
<p>
    Built with Blazor WebAssembly (.NET 8), Fluent UI components and Chart.js — hosted for
    free on GitHub Pages.
</p>

